    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hey @RedHeadphone, the idea is interesting. We're currently also discussing [an `AccessManager` implementation](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/4121) that might be suited for what you want to do.\r\n\r\nThere are still some open questions, but the particular use case of count/timestamp is not supported in the current design. We'd love to hear why you think that use-case could be important.\r\n\r\nIf we decide to support it, I'd say any access restriction should fall into our Access Control category, therefore added to the AccessManager.",
